<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573351>
    dc:description "Fig. 1.—A Dasypus hybridus from Saavedra, Buenos Aires Province, Argentina.Photograph byRicardoFernandez Chaves usedwith permission." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573351/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573355>
    dc:description "Fig. 2.—Osteoderms of different parts of the carapace of Dasypus hybridus: A) Movable bands, 20mm length by 5mm width; note the 3 triangular figures. B) Scapular and pelvic shields, 5mm length by 5mm width; note subcircular main figure and the small, peripheral figures. C) Head shield; note the lack of figures." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573355/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573353>
    dc:description "Fig. 3.—Dorsal, ventral, and lateral views of skull and lateral view of mandible of an adult male Dasypus hybridus (MLP 2421 [Facultad de Ciencias Naturales y Museo, Universidad Nacional de La Plata, Argentina, mammal collection]) from Coronel Dorrego, Buenos Aires Province, Argentina. Greatest length of skull is 70mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573353/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573357>
    dc:description "Fig. 4.—Geographic distribution (brown) of Dasypus hybridus. Map redrawn from Abba and Superina (2010) with modifications." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573357/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

